title: Google\Cloud\Notebooks\V1beta1\Instance
name: Instance
description:
The definition of a notebook instance.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.notebooks.v1beta1.Instance

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: Output only. The name of this notebook instance. Format: projects/{project_id}/locations/{location}/instances/{instance_id}

params.name: data.vm_image
params.description: Use a Compute Engine VM image to start the notebook instance.

params.name: data.container_image
params.description: Use a container image to start the notebook instance.

params.name: data.post_startup_script
params.description: Path to a Bash script that automatically runs after a notebook instance fully boots up. The path must be a URL or Cloud Storage path (gs://path-to-file/file-name).

params.name: data.proxy_uri
params.description: Output only. The proxy endpoint that is used to access the Jupyter notebook.

params.name: data.instance_owners
params.description: Input only. The owner of this instance after creation. Format: alias@example.com Currently supports one owner only. If not specified, all of the service account users of your VM instance's service account can use the instance.

params.name: data.service_account
params.description: The service account on this instance, giving access to other Google Cloud services. You can use any service account within the same project, but you must have the service account user permission to use the instance. If not specified, the Compute Engine default service account is used.

params.name: data.machine_type
params.description: Required. The Compute Engine machine type of this instance.

params.name: data.accelerator_config
params.description: The hardware accelerator used on this instance. If you use accelerators, make sure that your configuration has enough vCPUs and memory to support the machine_type you have selected.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Output only. The state of this instance.

params.name: data.install_gpu_driver
params.description: Whether the end user authorizes Google Cloud to install GPU driver on this instance. If this field is empty or set to false, the GPU driver won't be installed. Only applicable to instances with GPUs.

params.name: data.custom_gpu_driver_path
params.description: Specify a custom Cloud Storage path where the GPU driver is stored. If not specified, we'll automatically choose from official GPU drivers.

params.name: data.boot_disk_type
params.description: Input only. The type of the boot disk attached to this instance, defaults to standard persistent disk (PD_STANDARD).

params.name: data.boot_disk_size_gb
params.description: Input only. The size of the boot disk in GB attached to this instance, up to a maximum of 64000 GB (64 TB). The minimum recommended value is 100 GB. If not specified, this defaults to 100.

params.name: data.data_disk_type
params.description: Input only. The type of the data disk attached to this instance, defaults to standard persistent disk (PD_STANDARD).

params.name: data.data_disk_size_gb
params.description: Input only. The size of the data disk in GB attached to this instance, up to a maximum of 64000 GB (64 TB). You can choose the size of the data disk based on how big your notebooks and data are. If not specified, this defaults to 100.

params.name: data.no_remove_data_disk
params.description: Input only. If true, the data disk will not be auto deleted when deleting the instance.

params.name: data.disk_encryption
params.description: Input only. Disk encryption method used on the boot and data disks, defaults to GMEK.

params.name: data.kms_key
params.description: Input only. The KMS key used to encrypt the disks, only applicable if disk_encryption is CMEK. Format: projects/{project_id}/locations/{location}/keyRings/{key_ring_id}/cryptoKeys/{key_id} Learn more about using your own encryption keys.

params.name: data.no_public_ip
params.description: If true, no public IP will be assigned to this instance.

params.name: data.no_proxy_access
params.description: If true, the notebook instance will not register with the proxy.

params.name: data.network
params.description: The name of the VPC that this instance is in. Format: projects/{project_id}/global/networks/{network_id}

params.name: data.subnet
params.description: The name of the subnet that this instance is in. Format: projects/{project_id}/regions/{region}/subnetworks/{subnetwork_id}

params.name: data.labels
params.description: Labels to apply to this instance. These can be later modified by the setLabels method.

params.name: data.metadata
params.description: Custom metadata to apply to this instance.

params.name: data.nic_type
params.description: Optional. The type of vNIC to be used on this interface. This may be gVNIC or VirtioNet.

params.name: data.reservation_affinity
params.description: Optional. The optional reservation affinity. Setting this field will apply the specified Zonal Compute Reservation to this notebook instance.

params.name: data.can_ip_forward
params.description: Optional. Flag to enable ip forwarding or not, default false/off. https://cloud.google.com/vpc/docs/using-routes#canipforward

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: Output only. Instance creation time.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: Output only. Instance update time.
